What you need to know:

Mills said carrying the winning spirit in their training sessions will now be the key to their success in the Afro-basket festival scheduled for August 24 to September 5 in Kigali."How we prepare for the next challenge is critical. The players’ mindset is everything. Angola is a tough team and we know they will bring their “A” game next time we meet, so we'll need to clean up our act because we cannot afford any sloppy mistakes this time," said coach Mills. 